CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 23, 1945, p. 26, reads: "On Furlough - Corp. Raymond Walker and S2/C Carroll Walker were fortunate enough to spend their furloughs together, Raymond returning from the Central Pacific area, and Carroll home on furlough from the Great Lakes Training Center.   The brothers spent most of their time at home with Mr. and Mrs. Paul R. Williams, at 925 Anaheim Street, but visited their oldest sister, Audrey Walker Kelker, in Cleveland, Ohio.  They both have now returned to their stations. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Corporal Raymond Walker wearing U.S. Army uniform, and his brother Carroll Walker wearing U.S. Navy sailor uniform, posed in front of light colored background, Harris Studio
